1. create a new repo and go to code spaces. => create a new code space

2. Container: open Command palette from View in menu and type container. select node & JS.
this is a config file which is used to provide default node & JS to us. 
We can use the same process to get python & other languages as well.


3. Save : go to source control => select files which are changed => enter description => commit => go to more options => push

4. Stop code space : code spaces are available for only 120 per month. so after use we need to stop the useage by stopping it manually.